President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Oregon due to severe winter storms, flooding, landslides, and mudslides that occurred from February 23 to February 26, 2019. This declaration allows for Federal assistance to supplement State, tribal, and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. Federal funding will be available on a cost-sharing basis for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Rosalyn L. Cole has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for Federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the FEMA News Desk can be contacted at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.